item.title: CVE-2017-8199|2024-09-16T21:02:39.109Z -- huawei%20technologies%20co.%2C%20ltd. -- max%20presence%2Ctp3106%2Ctp3206%2C
item.description: MAX PRESENCE V100R001C00, TP3106 V100R002C00, TP3206 V100R002C00 have an out-of-bounds read vulnerability in H323 protocol. An attacker logs in to the system as a user and send crafted packets to the affected products. Due to insufficient verification of the packets, successful exploit will cause process reboot.

item.title: CVE-2017-8201|2024-09-16T22:25:15.407Z -- huawei%20technologies%20co.%2C%20ltd. -- max%20presence%2Ctp3106%2Ctp3206%2C
item.description: MAX PRESENCE V100R001C00, TP3106 V100R002C00, TP3206 V100R002C00 have an a memory leak vulnerability in H323 protocol. An attacker logs in to the system as a user and send crafted packets to the affected products. Due to insufficient verification of the packets, successful exploit could cause a memory leak and eventual denial of service (DoS) condition.
